which stage you think will be your biggest strength 
which stage you want to dig into a little more, or which stage you have uncertainties about


Please also jot down any questions to do with process expectations or any other areas of Bootcamp where you would like further clarification!

Excited to meet up!

content:

What questions do you have about the connection between the scoring system and writing projects?

Excited to discuss!

title: Antenna build for Kenwood At-180 ATU for UK Narrowboat QRP
content:
>The bands on my Kenwood AT-180 ATU are the following:
>
>MHz
>1,80
>3.80
>7,30
>14.20
>21.20
>28.50
>
>I have a narrowboat and intend to connect a "random wire" to the "Antenna 3" terminal.
>And am going to run the earth from the "GND" terminal to a copper pipe to place in the canal.
>
>Is this a good way to ground the set up or would I better grounding it to the actual steel boat hull?
>
>What is the optimum length for the random wire to make best use of the band coverage the ATU gives me?
>And what antenna cable would be the best to use?
>
>Likewise would AWG spec wire should I use from the "GND" Terminal to the copper pipe or steel hull?

Grounding the Kenwood AT-180 to the steel narrowboat hull provides a superior RF ground compared to a copper pipe in the canal. The hull acts as both a counterpoise and direct seawater connection, enhancing efficiency across HF bands, while a pipe may introduce higher resistance and corrosion issues.

| Length (m) | Closest Bands (MHz) | Wavelength Notes                |
| ---------- | ------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| 8.8        | 14.20, 21.20        | ~/10 at 20m, ~/16 at 15m qsl |
| 12.5       | 7.30, 14.20         | ~/16 at 40m, ~/22 at 20m qsl |
| 17.7       | 3.80, 1.80          | ~/16 at 80m, ~/11 at 75m qsl |

For Antenna 1 and 2 SO-239: Tuner  PL-259 connector  RG-58C/U coax  PL-259 connector  1:1 balun  14-12 AWG antenna wire (e.g., dipole legs). SEE below, balun at dipole end
The Antenna 3 screw terminal goes to 14-12 AWG wire. SORTED

Dipole Lengths Confirmation

Yes, split each length into two equal legs for center-fed dipoles on Antenna 1/2 SO-239 ports:

8.8m total  two 4.4m legs (targets 14.2/21.2 MHz)
12.5m total  two 6.25m legs (targets 7.3/14.2 MHz)
17.7m total  two 8.85m legs (targets 3.8/1.8 MHz)

Practical Trimming

Start 5% longer, prune for lowest SWR at band edges using AT-180 meter; boat mounting may shorten effective length by 3-5%.

Only one balun per dipole, installed at the antenna endtuner SO-239  RG-58C/U coax  balun at dipole  14-12 AWG legs.

https://www.hamradiostore.co.uk/ldg-rba-1-1-balun
https://moonrakeronline.com/ldg-rba-1-1-1-current-balun
LDG RBA-1 - 1:1 Current Balun

No, the LDG RBA-1:1 features a female SO-239 input for your RG-58C/U PL-259 plug, plus two top binding posts for dipole wire legs. Perfect feedpoint match.

Fit for Setup
Plugs directly into RG-58 end; attach 14 AWG wires to posts via ring terminalsweatherproof with silicone for canal use, QRP-ready 1.8-30 MHz.

RG8 Ultra Low Loss ideal compromiseminimal extra weight over RG-58
https://moonrakeronline.com/mini8-50-ohm-coax-cable-various-lenghts
OR
https://www.mcgillmicrowave.com/product/rg8/

Moonraker Mini8 vs McGill RG8

No, not the same: Moonraker Mini8 (6.1mm OD, RG8X-type, ~0.8 dB/30m loss at 1.8 MHz, 0.04 kg/m) is thinner/lighter/flexible low-loss. McGill RG8 (10.3mm OD true RG8, 1.0 dB/30m, 0.11 kg/m) thicker/heavier/higher power.

Mini8 vs LMR-400 Comparison

Moonraker Mini8 (RG8X-style) performs nearly as well as LMR-400 for your 30m QRP HFlosses ~0.9 dB/30m at 1.8 MHz (Mini8)
vs 0.7 dB (LMR-400), <0.3 dB difference irrelevant at 5W. Mini8 lighter (1.2kg/30m vs 3kg).

| Aspect           | Mini8        | LMR-400         |
| ---------------- | ------------ | --------------- |
| Loss 1.8 MHz/30m | 0.9 dB kv5r | 0.7 dB youtube |
| Weight/30m       | 1.2 kg       | 3 kg            |
| Flex/Dia         | High/6mm     | Med/10.3mm      |

https://moonrakeronline.com/pl259-compression-plug-7mm-for-mini-8

Antenna - Gauge: 4.0mm Diameter
https://moonrakeronline.com/original-pvc-flexweave-antenna-wire

Ground to hull
https://moonrakeronline.com/eu/32-heavy-duty-antenna-wire-made-with-kevlar

-export([start/2, stop/1]).

start(_StartType, _StartArgs) ->
    ip_fetcher_sup:start_link().

stop(_State) ->
    ok.

%% ===================================================================
%% Supervisor
%% ===================================================================

-module(ip_fetcher_sup).
-behaviour(supervisor).

-export([start_link/0, init/1]).

start_link() ->
    supervisor:start_link({local, ?MODULE}, ?MODULE, []).

init([]) ->
    SupFlags = #{
        strategy  => one_for_one,
        intensity => 3,        % max restarts
        period    => 5         % seconds
    },

    ChildSpec = #{
        id       => ip_fetcher,
        start    => {ip_fetcher_worker, start_link, []},
        restart  => transient, % only restart on abnormal exit
        shutdown => 5000,      % 5 seconds graceful shutdown
        type     => worker,
        modules  => [ip_fetcher_worker]
    },

    {ok, {SupFlags, [ChildSpec]}}.

%% ===================================================================
%% Worker
%% ===================================================================

-module(ip_fetcher_worker).
-behaviour(gen_server).

-export([start_link/0]).
-export([init/1, handle_call/3, handle_cast/2, handle_info/2, terminate/2, code_change/3]).

start_link() ->
    gen_server:start_link({local, ?MODULE}, ?MODULE, [], []).

init([]) ->
    % Start the work immediately
    self() ! fetch_ip,
    {ok, #{}}.

handle_call(_Request, _From, State) ->
    {reply, ok, State}.

handle_cast(_Msg, State) ->
    {noreply, State}.

handle_info(fetch_ip, State) ->
    case do_fetch_ip() of
        {ok, Ip} ->
            io:format("~s~n", [Ip]),
            % Normal exit  transient worker will NOT be restarted
            {stop, normal, State};
        {error, Reason} ->
            io:format("Failed to connect  will be restarted by supervisor: ~p~n", [Reason]),
            % Abnormal exit  supervisor WILL restart us (up to 3 times in 5s)
            {stop, {connect_failed, Reason}, State}
    end;

handle_info(_Info, State) ->
    {noreply, State}.

terminate(_Reason, _State) ->
    ok.

code_change(_OldVsn, State, _Extra) ->
    {ok, State}.

%% Internal function to fetch IP
do_fetch_ip() ->
    Host = "icanhazip.com",
    Port = 80,
    Timeout = 10000,

    case gen_tcp:connect(Host, Port, [binary, {active, false}], Timeout) of
        {ok, Socket} ->
            Request = "GET / HTTP/1.0\r\nHost: icanhazip.com\r\nConnection: close\r\n\r\n",
            ok = gen_tcp:send(Socket, Request),

            case recv_all(Socket, <<>>) of
                {ok, Data} ->
                    % Extract just the IP (last line)
                    Lines = binary:split(Data, <<"\n">>, [global, trim]),
                    Ip = lists:last(Lines),
                    gen_tcp:close(Socket),
                    {ok, binary_to_list(Ip)};
                Error ->
                    gen_tcp:close(Socket),
                    Error
            end;
        Error ->
            Error
    end.

recv_all(Socket, Acc) ->
    case gen_tcp:recv(Socket, 0, 10000) of
        {ok, Data} ->
            recv_all(Socket, <<Acc/binary, Data/binary>>);
        {error, closed} ->
            {ok, Acc};
        {error, _} = Err ->
            Err
    end.
